OL,3,CIslanders petition to stop conversion
OL,4,Cof Jersey Airport viewing area
OL,6,F"This is a profit-driven misuse of the
OL,7,Fspace and should be prevented at all
OL,8,Fcosts."
OL,10,FTowards the end of last year, Ports of
OL,11,FJersey announced its plans to
OL,12,Fredevelop Jersey Airport.
OL,14,FAdditions included a new duty-free
OL,15,Fshop, restaurant, a new seating area,
OL,16,Fand a children's play area.
OL,18,FHowever, there are concerns over the
OL,19,Fintroduction of a new No1 Lounge being
OL,20,Fintroduced to the space.
